title: German business groups file complaint over Apple privacy settings
description: Germany's media, internet and advertising industries on Monday filed an antitrust complaint against Apple Inc, alleging that new iPhone privacy settings represent a market abuse and a violation of competition law.  The filing, to the German Federal Cartel Office, came as Apple was due to roll out a new transparency framework that would require users to opt in to being tracked for the purpose of advertising.

title: Chart Advisor: Earnings Week
description: Stocks traded in a narrow range with indexes returning to their recent highs. This would normally be a bullish indication if the volatility indexes weren’t showing a divergence. The top two panels in the chart below compare the S&P 500 Index (SPX) with the Cboe Volatility Index (VIX). Below these is a comparison of the NASDAQ 100 Index (NDX) and the Cboe Nasdaq Volatility Index (VXN). The pattern for both comparisons is strikingly similar in nature because both volatility indexes are not at their lowest point. Conversely, the benchmark indexes are at their highest point.
